<div class="col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1 col-md-12">
  <h2>Options</h2>
  
  <h3>Application Environment Options</h3>
  
  <p><code>ember-datepicker</code> uses Ember CLI environment settings to include the stylesheet for highlighting syntax. This prevents the need for unnecessary styles being added to your vendor.css. To include your desired style add the following option to your <code>config/environment.js</code>.</p>
  
  {{#ember-highlight-code language="javascript"}}
    // config/environment.js
    module.exports = function(environment) {
      var ENV = {
        // ...
        'ember-datepicker': {
          theme: 'flick'
        }
      };
      // ...
      return ENV;
    };
  {{/ember-highlight-code}}
  
  <hr>
  
  <dl class="dl-horizontal">
    <dt>theme</dt>
    <dd>The code highlight style you want <code>ember-highlight-code</code> to use. To use a style, include the theme name from: <a href="https://github.com/components/jqueryui/tree/master/themes" target="_blank">jQuery UI themes</a>. A preview of the available themes can be accessed in the <a href="http://jqueryui.com/themeroller/" target="_blank">jQuery Themeroller</a>.</dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">string</span></dt>
    <dd><code>"flick"</code></dd>
  </dl>
  
  <h3>Component Options</h3>
  <dl class="dl-horizontal">
    <dt>inline</dt>
    <dd>Flag that determines if this picker is to be rendered as a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> or as an <code>&lt;input&gt;</code>.</dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">boolean</span></dt>
    <dd><code>true</code></dd>
    
    <dd class="clearfix">&nbsp;</dd>
    
    <dt>action</dt>
    <dd>The action to send back to the application when a date is selected.</dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">string</span></dt>
    <dd><code>null</code></dd>
    
    <dd class="clearfix">&nbsp;</dd>
    
    <dt>value</dt>
    <dd>The value that is associated with this picker.</dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">string</span></dt>
    <dd><code>null</code></dd>
    
    <dd class="clearfix">&nbsp;</dd>
    
    <dt>dateMarkers</dt>
    <dd>
      <p>The dates that have events.</p>
      <p><strong>Expected format:</strong></p>
      {{#ember-highlight-code}}
        var dates = {
          '2015-01-01': 2,
          '2015-01-05': 4,
          // ...
        };
      {{/ember-highlight-code}}
    </dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">object</span></dt>
    <dd><code>{}</code></dd>
    
    <dd class="clearfix">&nbsp;</dd>
    
    <dt>dateFormat</dt>
    <dd>The format for the date. Reference: <a href="http://api.jqueryui.com/datepicker/#utility-formatDate" target="_blank">jQuery Datepicker Widget API Docs</a></dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">jQuery Datepicker Date</span></dt>
    <dd><code>"yy-mm-dd"</code></dd>
    
    <dd class="clearfix">&nbsp;</dd>
    
    <dt>changeMonth</dt>
    <dd>If <code>true</code>, show dropdown menu for month selection.</dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">boolean</span></dt>
    <dd><code>false</code></dd>
    
    <dd class="clearfix">&nbsp;</dd>
    
    <dt>changeYear</dt>
    <dd>If <code>true</code>, show dropdown menu for year selection.</dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">boolean</span></dt>
    <dd><code>false</code></dd>
  
    <dd class="clearfix">&nbsp;</dd>
    
    <dt>dateWithEventsClass</dt>
    <dd>The class to be applied for dates with events.</dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">string</span></dt>
    <dd><code>"date-with-events"</code></dd>
  
    <dd class="clearfix">&nbsp;</dd>
    
    <dt>dateNoEventsClass</dt>
    <dd>The class to be applied for dates without events.</dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">string</span></dt>
    <dd><code>"date-no-events"</code></dd>
  
    <dd class="clearfix">&nbsp;</dd>
    
    <dt>minDate</dt>
    <dd>The minimum selectable date on the picker. Value can be either a valid <a href="http://momentjs.com/docs/#/displaying/format/" target="_blank">moment.js date</a> string or a valid <a href="http://api.jqueryui.com/datepicker/#option-minDate" target="_blank">jQUery Datepicker Widget</a> date string.</dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">string</span></dt>
    <dd><code>null</code></dd>
  
    <dd class="clearfix">&nbsp;</dd>
    
    <dt>maxDate</dt>
    <dd>The maximum selectable date on the picker. Value can be either a valid <a href="http://momentjs.com/docs/#/displaying/format/" target="_blank">moment.js date</a> string or a valid <a href="http://api.jqueryui.com/datepicker/#option-maxDate" target="_blank">jQUery Datepicker Widget</a> date string.</dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">string</span></dt>
    <dd><code>null</code></dd>
  
    <dd class="clearfix">&nbsp;</dd>
    
    <dt>markerTooltipPrefix</dt>
    <dd>The prefix for the tooltips on dates that have events.</dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">string</span></dt>
    <dd><code>""</code></dd>
    
    <dd class="clearfix">&nbsp;</dd>
    
    <dt>markerTooltipSuffix</dt>
    <dd>The suffix for the tooltips on dates that have events.</dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">string</span></dt>
    <dd><code>" events"</code></dd>
    
    <dd class="clearfix">&nbsp;</dd>
    
    <dt>daysWithoutEventsSelectable</dt>
    <dd>Whether or not the dates that do not have events whould be selectable.</dd>
    <dt><span class="small text-muted">boolean</span></dt>
    <dd><code>true</code></dd>
  </dl>
